SIMPLE: boning
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Boning
<hw>Bon"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Senses 1 and 2 fr. 1st
<er>Bone</er>, sense 3 fr. 3d <er>Bone</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
clearing of bones from fish or meat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The manuring of land with bones.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A method of leveling a line or surface by sighting
along the tops of two or more straight edges, or a range of properly
spaced poles. See 3d <er>Bone</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bonitary</ent>⟦br⟧
